               <p>JOHN PIPER. I live in Wheeler-street. I was walking with my wife at the end of <placeName id="t18340410-214-crimeloc1218">Church-street, Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340410-214-crimeloc1218" type="placeName" value="Church-street, Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340410-214-crimeloc1218" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340410-214-off1216 t18340410-214-crimeloc1218"></join>, on the 5th of April, at a quarter before ten o'clock at night - I felt the prisoner's hand in my pocket - I turned round, and seized the prisoner as he was taking his hand away from my pocket - at the same time I kicked against my handkerchief on the ground - I said, "What did you touch my pocket for?" - my wife turned and said, "Here is your handkerchief" - I held the prisoner three or four minutes - he threatened if I did not let him go he would give me a b-y punch of the head - there was another with the prisoner, and he threatened me also - I let the prisoner go, and they both went about twenty yards down the street - they turned down a street, and both ran off - I turned back, and walked with my wife down Shoreditch, and met them both again - I then gave the prisoner in charge - I am positive he is the person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340410-214-person1387">
                  SARAH 
                  PIPER
               <interp inst="t18340410-214-person1387" type="surname" value="PIPER"></interp>
